1
00:00:44,799 --> 00:00:45,320
Ruojin.

2
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:46,439
Ruojin.

3
00:00:52,520 --> 00:00:54,200
Then why did you hurt Xu Ruojin?

4
00:00:54,679 --> 00:00:56,399
She has nothing to do with any of this.

5
00:00:56,679 --> 00:00:58,359
Xu Ruojin didn't die, did she?

6
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,960
How much did the Wangs pay you?

7
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:05,400
For you to sell your soul to them.

8
00:01:10,480 --> 00:01:12,200
I never cared about the money.

9
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:13,040
Then what is it?

10
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:14,519
Because of you.

11
00:01:19,159 --> 00:01:23,239
Three-Seed Decoction clears damp-heat.

12
00:01:23,799 --> 00:01:26,120
It needs Apricot Kernel,

13
00:01:26,599 --> 00:01:28,000
Coix Seed,

14
00:01:28,959 --> 00:01:33,799
Cardamom, Talc, Pinellia,

15
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:35,519
Tetrapanax Pith...

16
00:01:36,319 --> 00:01:38,400
Tetrapanax Pith...

17
00:01:42,959 --> 00:01:44,439
Feifan, you tell me.

18
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:46,680
I don't know either.

19
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:48,680
I really don't.

20
00:01:49,599 --> 00:01:51,840
And Bamboo Leaf and Magnolia Bark.

21
00:01:52,359 --> 00:01:53,719
You knew. Why didn't you say so?

22
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:57,280
I don't need you to go easy on me.

23
00:02:00,159 --> 00:02:01,840
I've had nothing since I was a child.

24
00:02:02,879 --> 00:02:04,920
I treated Master and Master's wife as family.

25
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:06,640
But they...

26
00:02:07,719 --> 00:02:08,680
Putting on airs.

27
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:09,599
Fake kindness, phony virtue.

28
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:11,639
They only had eyes for you.

29
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:13,759
What do you have?

30
00:02:14,879 --> 00:02:16,919
You just happen to share their blood.

31
00:02:19,319 --> 00:02:22,240
Why must I live forever in your shadow?

32
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:25,360
That prescription...

33
00:02:25,719 --> 00:02:27,439
we came up with it together.

34
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:30,599
But everyone gave you all the credit.

35
00:02:31,719 --> 00:02:32,560
How is that fair?

36
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:34,319
Why?

37
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:46,479
Hurry up and search!

38
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:47,159
Yes, sir.

39
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,240
Move.

40
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:45,319
Yes, sir.

41
00:03:47,199 --> 00:03:48,919
I want everyone to know

42
00:03:49,439 --> 00:03:50,840
that they were all wrong.

43
00:03:51,439 --> 00:03:52,520
All wrong.

44
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:59,800
And for that, you killed my whole family?

45
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:07,319
Junior Brother, when it comes down to it,

46
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:09,759
you should actually thank me.

47
00:04:21,759 --> 00:04:22,240
Dad.

48
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:28,040
You're still alive.

49
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:30,279
As you can see,

50
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,040
I'm doing quite well.

51
00:05:11,759 --> 00:05:12,680
Where is he?

52
00:05:13,839 --> 00:05:16,319
In a very beautiful place.

53
00:05:17,079 --> 00:05:17,800
Where?

54
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:21,120
Come on, Junior Brother.

55
00:05:22,639 --> 00:05:23,600
Someone like you?

56
00:05:24,279 --> 00:05:25,040
You can't save him.

57
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:30,399
Where is he?

58
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:32,519
I don't know.

59
00:05:33,519 --> 00:05:34,000
Where?

60
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:35,279
He's...

61
00:05:35,639 --> 00:05:36,879
in Wang Wenhao's hands.

62
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:47,800
Wang Wenhao.

63
00:06:01,279 --> 00:06:04,439
You got three herbs wrong in Formula 37 of Treatise on Febrile Diseases.

64
00:06:05,319 --> 00:06:05,839
Keep squatting.

65
00:06:07,439 --> 00:06:09,079
You mixed up Angelica with Atractylodes.

66
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:09,959
Atractylodes.

67
00:06:11,439 --> 00:06:13,240
You wrote Arisaema instead of Pinellia.

68
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:14,120
Arisaema.

69
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:17,279
Not one herb in a prescription can be wrong.

70
00:06:17,959 --> 00:06:20,160
A miss is as good as a mile.

71
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:26,079
One wrong herb costs a life.

72
00:06:27,439 --> 00:06:28,079
Do you understand?

73
00:06:28,279 --> 00:06:30,079
Yes, Dad. I won't make that mistake again.

74
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:31,399
Do you understand?

75
00:06:33,759 --> 00:06:34,600
Keep squatting.

76
00:06:38,959 --> 00:06:39,800
Keep squatting.

77
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:42,480
Brother.

78
00:06:43,439 --> 00:06:44,680
If you make that prescription,

79
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:47,360
can it really save Dad from Wang Wenhao?

80
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:51,439
All of this...

81
00:06:52,639 --> 00:06:53,519
Dazhuang's death...

82
00:06:53,519 --> 00:06:54,800
Did Brother Hui really do it?

83
00:06:57,839 --> 00:06:58,560
Forget about him.

84
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:02,720
Are Dazhuang's funeral arrangements settled?

85
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:07,759
This was his most precious possession.

86
00:07:27,079 --> 00:07:28,879
He's already written so much.

87
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:31,240
He definitely would have been

88
00:07:32,319 --> 00:07:33,000
a great doctor.

89
00:07:59,240 --> 00:07:59,720
Master.

90
00:08:00,639 --> 00:08:01,079
What's this?

91
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:02,879
Six qian.

92
00:08:03,399 --> 00:08:04,079
Angelica.

93
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:06,920
Why Angelica?

94
00:08:07,439 --> 00:08:09,040
Angelica and Earthworm can't be combined.

95
00:08:10,279 --> 00:08:10,600
Change it.

96
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:11,959
Six qian of Goji Berry.

97
00:08:12,639 --> 00:08:12,879
Alright.

98
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:20,399
Remember this well.

99
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:22,879
A miss is as good as a mile.

100
00:08:23,399 --> 00:08:24,279
One wrong herb...

101
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:26,439
...costs a life.

102
00:08:29,279 --> 00:08:30,040
Understood, Master.

103
00:08:30,319 --> 00:08:31,240
I'll make sure to remember.

104
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:32,919
Thank you, Master.

105
00:08:46,679 --> 00:08:48,480
You mixed up Angelica with Atractylodes.

106
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:49,480
Atractylodes.

107
00:08:50,559 --> 00:08:52,200
You wrote Arisaema instead of Pinellia.

108
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:53,320
Arisaema.

109
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:57,080
Not one herb in a prescription can be wrong.

110
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:00,159
A miss is as good as a mile.

111
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:22,559
Brother.

112
00:09:23,399 --> 00:09:24,320
What kind of prescription is this?

113
00:09:25,039 --> 00:09:25,960
One that saves lives.

114
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:38,159
Wu Hui.

115
00:09:38,679 --> 00:09:39,840
We're from the North City Police Department.

116
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:41,159
You're under arrest.

117
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:42,120
Here's the warrant.

118
00:10:02,279 --> 00:10:03,440
Well played, Doctor Ren.

119
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:05,600
Playing pretty rough.

120
00:10:07,279 --> 00:10:09,480
Sending your childhood friend to prison.

121
00:10:11,759 --> 00:10:12,200
Speak.

122
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:14,360
What do you want from me?

123
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:18,440
Let's make a deal.

124
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:20,039
What kind of deal?

125
00:10:25,399 --> 00:10:27,080
I have what you need.

126
00:10:36,759 --> 00:10:37,600
Ren Feifan.

127
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:41,440
This new formulation of yours is terrifying.

128
00:10:42,919 --> 00:10:44,000
Are you trying to kill me?

129
00:10:46,159 --> 00:10:47,679
Extraordinary medicine yields extraordinary results.

130
00:10:48,519 --> 00:10:49,480
The formulation of a prescription

131
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:51,960
requires both boldness and precision.

132
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:53,840
The previous dosage

133
00:10:55,919 --> 00:10:56,840
you tested for four years

134
00:10:57,279 --> 00:10:58,000
and never succeeded.

135
00:10:59,679 --> 00:11:01,399
You've got nothing to lose by trying this.

136
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:04,039
Formulation is a craft.

137
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:05,679
Only experienced pharmacists

138
00:11:06,399 --> 00:11:08,240
know how to blend these herbs.

139
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:14,240
Why should I trust you?

140
00:11:18,639 --> 00:11:20,080
My father is in your hands.

141
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:22,840
I won't gamble with his life.

142
00:11:29,519 --> 00:11:29,879
Fine.

143
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:32,600
I'll trust you for now.

144
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:34,279
When can I see him?

145
00:12:22,879 --> 00:12:24,320
Master Ren, your food is here.

146
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:25,840
Okay.

147
00:12:27,279 --> 00:12:27,679
Pebble.

148
00:12:27,679 --> 00:12:28,000
Yeah?

149
00:12:29,679 --> 00:12:30,759
You've taken care of me for so long,

150
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:34,039
but I never asked what your parents do.

151
00:12:34,679 --> 00:12:36,080
I've been an orphan since I was little.

152
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:39,159
Villagers say I sprang out from a crack in a rock,

153
00:12:39,159 --> 00:12:40,360
so they call me Pebble.

154
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:43,559
Master Ren,

155
00:12:43,879 --> 00:12:44,879
you're a good person.

156
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:46,639
They're all bad people.

157
00:12:48,679 --> 00:12:50,080
You're a clever kid.

158
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:51,879
Why don't you run away?
